[KATO] Well now...
guess we're gonna have to work
on that sense of humor.

94
00:06:03,373 --> 00:06:06,407
[LELEI] If I don't have one it's
because of your teaching.

95
00:06:12,940 --> 00:06:14,273
[KATO] We're not moving...

96
00:06:14,373 --> 00:06:16,873
I don't suppose you overloaded
the cart?

97
00:06:16,973 --> 00:06:18,973
[LELEI] You wanted all of your
books, Master...

98
00:06:19,073 --> 00:06:21,707
you should've expected something
like this.

99
00:06:21,807 --> 00:06:23,073
[KATO] It's a good thing we're
wizards...

100
00:06:23,173 --> 00:06:24,507
let's just magic it out.

101
00:06:24,607 --> 00:06:27,040
[LELEI] "Magic is the world's
most sacred thing ..."

102
00:06:27,140 --> 00:06:29,707
"It should never be used for
trivial matters!"

103
00:06:29,807 --> 00:06:31,307
[LELEI] Your words,
if I remember.

104
00:06:31,407 --> 00:06:33,007
[KATO] Yeah, well...

105
00:06:33,107 --> 00:06:35,507
[LELEI] But in this case I
believe we're out of options ...

106
00:06:43,673 --> 00:06:45,073
[KATO] I'm... sorry.

107
00:06:45,173 --> 00:06:49,873
[LELEI] It's fine. I've gotten
used to it... Master.

108
00:06:53,207 --> 00:06:56,807
Huh? What's going on? Why are we
just sitting here?

109
00:06:56,907 --> 00:06:58,907
[VILLAGER ] Master Kato...!
Lelei...!

110
00:06:59,007 --> 00:07:01,140
The road is being blocked by a
carriage's broken down!

111
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:03,307
Someone overloaded and snapped
the axle!

112
00:07:03,407 --> 00:07:05,573
[KUWABARA] Let's get this column
moving, people.

113
00:07:05,673 --> 00:07:07,040
[BOTH] Uh... Huh?

114
00:07:07,140 --> 00:07:08,973
[KUWABARA] Hey, Lieutenant!
Look in that book of yours

115
00:07:09,073 --> 00:07:10,540
and tell the Chief we need some
help!

116
00:07:10,640 --> 00:07:11,873
[YOJI] Got it, Old School!

117
00:07:11,973 --> 00:07:14,307
[KATO] never heard a
language like that before.

118
00:07:14,407 --> 00:07:16,373
[LELEI] I've never seen clothes
like that before.

119
00:07:16,473 --> 00:07:18,407
[KUWABARA] Kurokawa. Check
around for injuries!

120
00:07:18,507 --> 00:07:19,607
[MARI] Yes, sergeant major!

121
00:07:19,707 --> 00:07:22,907
[KATO] A woman... who's also a
soldier?

122
00:07:23,007 --> 00:07:24,873
I shall go take a look, Master.

123
00:07:24,973 --> 00:07:27,473
[KATO] Huh? Wait a minute!
Lelei!

124
00:07:33,840 --> 00:07:36,240
(horse in distress)

125
00:07:42,340 --> 00:07:44,307
[LELEI] Life‐threatening
injuries...

126
00:07:47,273 --> 00:07:49,840
[MARI] It looks like she might
have a concussion...

127
00:07:49,940 --> 00:07:53,107
looks like her ribs might be
broken, too.

128
00:07:53,207 --> 00:07:55,740
[FURUTA] Please! It's not safe
here!

129
00:07:55,840 --> 00:07:57,407
[LELEI] You're a healer? Uh!

130
00:07:57,507 --> 00:07:59,973
(panicked horse)

131
00:08:21,573 --> 00:08:23,373
[MARI] Hey! Are you okay?

132
00:08:25,540 --> 00:08:26,973
[LELEI] These people...

133
00:08:27,940 --> 00:08:30,040
[LELEI] ...these people just
saved my life.

134
00:08:31,107 --> 00:08:32,607
[KURATA] Lieutenant...

135
00:08:32,707 --> 00:08:34,040
[KURATA] How long do you think

136
00:08:34,140 --> 00:08:36,873
we're supposed take care of all
these folks anyway?

137
00:08:37,607 --> 00:08:38,707
[YOJI] What's that?

138
00:08:38,807 --> 00:08:40,040
[KURATA] Don't they have some
kind of

139
00:08:40,140 --> 00:08:42,040
noble lords or whatever to look
after them?

140
00:08:42,140 --> 00:08:44,607
[YOJI] Well, I asked about it.
[KURATA] Uh?

141
00:08:44,707 --> 00:08:47,273
[YOJI] I bounced it off the
chief when we were talking.

142
00:08:47,373 --> 00:08:49,507
The lord over this area took his
army with him

143
00:08:49,607 --> 00:08:52,040
and they ended up part of the
body count at Alnus Hill.

144
00:08:52,140 --> 00:08:54,807
[YOJI] We wiped all of them out,
Kurata. All of them.

145
00:09:03,407 --> 00:09:06,373
[BANDIT] I heard everyone in
Coda is bailing out tonight.

146
00:09:06,473 --> 00:09:08,507
[BANDIT BOSS] Sounds like easy
pickins for like us.

147
00:09:08,607 --> 00:09:10,707
[BANDIT] It's not like we got a
lot of guys, man!

148
00:09:10,807 --> 00:09:12,640
[BANDIT BOSS] Well check this
out.

149
00:09:12,740 --> 00:09:14,607
a buncha defeated soldiers
camping out...

150
00:09:14,707 --> 00:09:16,940
they'll jump at the chance to
join us.

151
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:18,740
[BANDIT BOSS] We offer those
guys a little something,

152
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:20,107
we can make an army of our own

153
00:09:20,207 --> 00:09:22,073
and take down an entire city!

154
00:09:22,173 --> 00:09:25,007
[BANDIT] And force a lord out of
the area!

155
00:09:25,107 --> 00:09:28,040
[BOSS] Eheh! From leading a
bunch of troublemakers,

156
00:09:28,140 --> 00:09:29,973
to having my own city...

157
00:09:31,207 --> 00:09:33,040
I like it.

158
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:46,140
[RORY] (giggle) [RORY] Good
evening, gentlemen!

159
00:09:48,273 --> 00:09:51,173
[RORY] I'm so glad you could all
get together like this.

160
00:09:55,107 --> 00:09:56,940
[RORY] And... I am very thankful

161
00:09:57,040 --> 00:10:00,073
for you offering your lives to
charity...

162
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:03,773
[RORY] The Supreme God... loves
the way

163
00:10:03,873 --> 00:10:06,807
you naughty boys have behaved
yourselves.

164
00:10:06,907 --> 00:10:11,373
[RORY] You should be honored
he's asked you to join him... in
the afterlife!

165
00:10:14,873 --> 00:10:17,040
[RORY] (giggles)

166
00:10:17,140 --> 00:10:20,173
[RORY] You may call me Rory
Mercury.

167
00:10:20,273 --> 00:10:24,040
[RORY] I am an apostle...
of the Dark God Emroy.

168
00:10:28,273 --> 00:10:31,373
[BANDIT] Holy shit it's really
her! It's Rory the Reaper!

169
00:10:31,473 --> 00:10:33,073
[BANDIT] The gown!

170
00:10:33,173 --> 00:10:36,773
The Temple of Emroy's
Oracle Robe!

171
00:10:36,873 --> 00:10:38,207
[BANDIT] Get outta here!

172
00:10:39,007 --> 00:10:40,307
[RORY] No you don't...

173
00:11:24,714 --> 00:11:25,674
[MARI] One‐twenty over eighty.

174
00:11:25,774 --> 00:11:27,841
She'll be up and around pretty
soon, sir.

175
00:11:27,941 --> 00:11:32,408
[YOJI] That's good... but... not
sure she wants to.

176
00:11:32,508 --> 00:11:35,441
[KURATA] So, have any of 'em
said where they're going?

177
00:11:35,541 --> 00:11:37,041
[YOJI] Hmm?

178
00:11:37,574 --> 00:11:38,974
Nope. Not really.

179
00:11:39,074 --> 00:11:41,008
[KURATA] Huh? You're kidding
right?

180
00:11:42,408 --> 00:11:44,341
[YOJI] (sigh) Leading an
evacuation effort,

181
00:11:44,441 --> 00:11:46,308
is a lot more tiring than I
thought it'd be.

182
00:11:46,408 --> 00:11:50,841
[KATO] Ahhh... I really need a
drink of water...

183
00:11:50,941 --> 00:11:53,574
[LELEI] We won't be able to stop
for a while.

184
00:11:55,074 --> 00:11:59,708
[KUWABARA] Comer on. Move it!
Get your backs into it!

185
00:11:59,808 --> 00:12:01,141
[KUWABARA] Move it!

186
00:12:04,741 --> 00:12:07,108
[YOJI] So here's the thing...
If they have to pick a spot

187
00:12:07,208 --> 00:12:10,941
it's gonna be in a place
where the dragon can't get them.

188
00:12:11,041 --> 00:12:12,941
It's the same for any refugee
no matter where you live.

189
00:12:13,041 --> 00:12:15,974
Except for the whole dragon
part.

190
00:12:16,074 --> 00:12:19,408
[TOMITA] It's not gonna work,
sir. The axle snapped.

191
00:12:19,508 --> 00:12:23,874
[VILLAGE CHIEF] If we
stay we're only sentencing
ourselves to die.

192
00:12:23,974 --> 00:12:34,441
Only carry what is necessary.
Leave the rest.

193
00:12:34,541 --> 00:12:36,708
[VILLAGER] Uh... Fine. I get it.

194
00:12:36,808 --> 00:12:40,074
[SON] (crying)

195
00:12:40,174 --> 00:12:43,241
[MARI] So why did you make them
burn it, Lieutenant?

196
00:12:43,341 --> 00:12:45,474
[YOJI] Because they were just
sitting in front of their stuff

197
00:12:45,574 --> 00:12:46,608
and wouldn't leave it behind.

198
00:12:46,708 --> 00:12:48,108
I suppose you have a better
idea?

199
00:12:48,208 --> 00:12:51,208
[MARI] We could have put in a
call for more vehicles.

200
00:12:51,308 --> 00:12:52,741
[YOJI] Take a peek at your map
and

201
00:12:52,841 --> 00:12:54,774
you'll see we're behind enemy
lines already.

202
00:12:54,874 --> 00:12:56,674
[YOJI] I mean they might let a
few vehicles get by,

203
00:12:56,774 --> 00:13:01,074
but if we bring too many in, it
could get real ugly real fast.

204
00:13:01,174 --> 00:13:03,141
[YOJI] They shoot at us, we call
in a strike,

205
00:13:03,241 --> 00:13:04,741
they die, more take their place,

206
00:13:04,841 --> 00:13:06,674
then it's an air strike, and
we've pretty much

207
00:13:06,774 --> 00:13:07,974
failed the mission we were given

208
00:13:08,074 --> 00:13:09,741
to establish peaceful relations

209
00:13:09,841 --> 00:13:11,374
We'd end up escalating the
conflict

210
00:13:11,474 --> 00:13:12,874
trying to help them out.

211
00:13:12,974 --> 00:13:16,341
So we won't be able to get more
vehicles... understand?

212
00:13:19,074 --> 00:13:20,808
[MARI] Guess the major told you
that in advance.

213
00:13:20,908 --> 00:13:23,608
[YOJI] We have to help them
out as best we can...

214
00:13:23,708 --> 00:13:25,674
cause nobody's gonna help us,
got it?

215
00:13:25,774 --> 00:13:28,041
[MARI] Oh? Huh?

216
00:13:28,141 --> 00:13:29,974
[KURATA] What's that?

217
00:13:30,074 --> 00:13:32,574
[KURATA] I see something...
up the road.

218
00:13:36,341 --> 00:13:37,574
[YOJI] Crows?

219
00:13:42,574 --> 00:13:44,041
[YOJI] No... way...

220
00:13:46,608 --> 00:13:47,741
[YOJI] Goth lolita girl!

221
00:13:47,841 --> 00:13:49,008
[KURATA] What'd you say?

222
00:13:50,508 --> 00:13:52,341
[RORY] (giggle)

223
