sure are young.

229
00:14:09,874 --> 00:14:11,308
[BOY] She's an oracle!

230
00:14:11,908 --> 00:14:12,774
[BOY] Oracle!

231
00:14:12,874 --> 00:14:14,141
[BOY] Hey, Oracle!

232
00:14:14,241 --> 00:14:15,574
[YOJI] Oracle?

233
00:14:15,674 --> 00:14:18,741
[RORY] And where are you kids
from?
[BOY] Coda Village, Ma'am.

234
00:14:18,841 --> 00:14:21,074
[OLD LADY] We're running away
from our village.
It was attacked.

235
00:14:21,174 --> 00:14:24,541
A flame dragon appeared...
so we evacuated.

236
00:14:24,641 --> 00:14:26,974
It almost looks like they're
praying to her doesn't it?

237
00:14:27,074 --> 00:14:29,141
[YOJI] Do you think maybe that
fancy outfit of hers

238
00:14:29,241 --> 00:14:31,308
has a special meaning or
something?

239
00:14:33,741 --> 00:14:35,074
[RORY] Oh...?

240
00:14:36,408 --> 00:14:38,574
[RORY] So who are these
strangers you're with?

241
00:14:38,674 --> 00:14:39,808
[BOY] They came and helped us
out!

242
00:14:39,908 --> 00:14:41,441
They're the good guys!

243
00:14:41,541 --> 00:14:44,308
[RORY] And you're sure
they're not taking you
against your will?

244
00:14:44,408 --> 00:14:45,374
[BOY] Mm‐mm!

245
00:14:45,474 --> 00:14:47,974
So how is this moving
without any horses?

246
00:14:48,074 --> 00:14:50,074
[BOY] I... don't know. But one
thing for certain

247
00:14:50,174 --> 00:14:52,174
it's a lot more comfortable than
a carriage!

248
00:14:52,274 --> 00:14:56,541
[RORY] Really? More comfortable
than a carriage?

249
00:14:59,274 --> 00:15:01,974
[RORY] Well I would just love
for you to show me...

250
00:15:02,074 --> 00:15:04,608
how "comfortable" the ride is.

251
00:15:04,708 --> 00:15:06,541
[YOJI] Uh... Za...

252
00:15:06,641 --> 00:15:09,374
Zavalu. Halu uguluu? Hehe...

253
00:15:10,508 --> 00:15:12,941
[RORY] (giggle)

254
00:15:19,941 --> 00:15:21,441
(discomfort)

255
00:15:21,541 --> 00:15:24,141
[YOJI] Hey! Hang on a second...!

256
00:15:24,241 --> 00:15:26,308
[YOJI] That is not where you
sit!

257
00:15:27,008 --> 00:15:28,274
[YOJI] Please just move!

258
00:15:28,374 --> 00:15:29,941
[KURATA] How is this happening
to you right now?!

259
00:15:30,041 --> 00:15:31,841
[YOJI] I just need you to get
off, okay!

260
00:15:31,941 --> 00:15:33,141
[RORY] Oh! really?

261
00:15:33,241 --> 00:15:34,874
[YOJI] Don't touch my gun!
That's dangerous!

262
00:15:34,974 --> 00:15:36,641
[RORY] Ehhh?
[YOJI] Keep your hands off!

263
00:15:36,741 --> 00:15:37,708
[KURATA]You're the luckiest guy
ever!

264
00:15:37,808 --> 00:15:38,874
[YOJI] I'm not enjoying this!

265
00:15:38,974 --> 00:15:40,641
[RORY] Oop‐sie!

266
00:15:40,741 --> 00:15:41,774
[KURATA] I'm dyin' over here!

267
00:15:41,874 --> 00:15:43,574
[YOJI] Hey! That thing is
loaded!

268
00:15:43,674 --> 00:15:45,241
I mean it! Get off of
me!

269
00:15:48,074 --> 00:15:50,341
[VILLAGER] Oh, look it's Roche
Hill.

270
00:15:50,441 --> 00:15:53,141
[VILLAGER] I can't believe we
walked so far!

271
00:15:53,241 --> 00:15:55,141
[KURATA] The terrain's starting
to look a little different.

272
00:15:55,241 --> 00:15:57,374
[YOJI] Yeah... we really put
some distance

273
00:15:57,474 --> 00:15:59,074
between us and the village.

274
00:16:00,308 --> 00:16:03,041
I really hope we get this whole
evacuation over with.

275
00:16:03,141 --> 00:16:05,208
[KURATA] A‐men to that, sir.

276
00:16:21,374 --> 00:16:23,508
[YOJI] It sure gets a lot hotter
out here

277
00:16:23,608 --> 00:16:25,408
than it does in Japan, you know?

278
00:16:36,441 --> 00:16:37,674
[YOJI] Wha‐?!

279
00:16:37,774 --> 00:16:38,808
Contact!

280
00:17:00,774 --> 00:17:02,341
[KATO] An honest to goodness
flame dragon!

281
00:17:02,441 --> 00:17:05,208
[KATO] I've never actually seen
one! Wahhahhhh!

282
00:17:14,974 --> 00:17:18,074
[KUWABARA] I know it's the
tradition of the self defense
force to fight for the people,

283
00:17:18,174 --> 00:17:20,174
but we might wanna run!

284
00:17:22,074 --> 00:17:24,908
[YOJI] I need a diversion,
Katsumoto! 50 CAL!

285
00:17:29,141 --> 00:17:31,008
[YOJI] Don't let up! Keep on
shooting!

286
00:17:31,108 --> 00:17:33,541
It's gotta have a weakness
somewhere!!

287
00:17:36,174 --> 00:17:37,541
[YOJI] Watch out, guys!

288
00:17:44,174 --> 00:17:46,108
[KURATA] That thing could fry us
all in a second!

289
00:17:46,208 --> 00:17:48,074
[YOJI] 50 cal isn't making a
dent!

290
00:17:53,741 --> 00:17:55,874
[YOJI] Shit! Come on!

291
00:18:03,474 --> 00:18:06,308
[TUKA] ONO!
[YOJI] Huh?! Well look who's up!

292
00:18:07,341 --> 00:18:08,541
[TUKA] O‐NO!

293
00:18:08,641 --> 00:18:10,508
[TUKA] O‐NO!

294
00:18:10,608 --> 00:18:11,574
[YOJI] What?

295
00:18:20,208 --> 00:18:22,174
[YOJI] The eyes! Aim for the
eyes!

296
00:18:26,541 --> 00:18:28,808
[DRAGON] (growl)

297
00:18:29,874 --> 00:18:32,508
(roars in pain)

298
00:18:38,241 --> 00:18:40,808
[YOJI] He didn't like that. RPG!

299
00:18:42,308 --> 00:18:45,308
[KATSUMOTO] Oops... better check
my rear.

300
00:18:45,408 --> 00:18:46,574
[ALL] Just shoot it!

301
00:18:51,374 --> 00:18:52,908
[YOJI] You pulled it!

302
00:18:53,008 --> 00:18:54,441
[YOJI] It's not gonna hit!

303
00:19:17,941 --> 00:19:19,474
(roar of rage and pain)

304
00:19:40,708 --> 00:19:43,274
[KURATA] That... was kind of
awesome.

305
00:19:44,241 --> 00:19:46,074
[YOJI] Well, glad you had fun.

306
00:20:04,308 --> 00:20:09,474
[VILLAGERS] (lamenting, crying,
moaning)

307
00:20:12,541 --> 00:20:15,408
[GIRL] (sobbing)

308
00:20:29,471 --> 00:20:30,247
[KUWABARA] Most of the survivors

309
00:20:30,347 --> 00:20:32,247
have relatives they can stay
with nearby.

310
00:20:32,347 --> 00:20:35,614
[KUWABARA] And a few others
have arrangements for shelter
and lodging.

311
00:20:35,714 --> 00:20:38,981
[YOJI] What about the rest?
Are they sure they're gonna be
able to find something...?

312
00:20:39,081 --> 00:20:40,881
If they're on their own out
there?

313
00:20:40,981 --> 00:20:42,147
[KUWABARA] I hope so,

314
00:20:42,247 --> 00:20:44,181
but we've got a bigger issue to
deal with.

315
00:20:44,281 --> 00:20:46,181
[YOJI] A lot of kids and older
folks...

316
00:20:46,281 --> 00:20:49,147
lost their family... in the last
attack.

317
00:20:49,247 --> 00:20:51,047
[VILLAGE CHIEF] It might seem
heartless,

318
00:20:51,147 --> 00:20:53,947
but we have our hands full
trying to find another place to
live.

319
00:20:54,047 --> 00:20:56,147
We simply can't stretch
ourselves any thinner

320
00:20:56,247 --> 00:20:57,514
adding someone else.

321
00:20:57,614 --> 00:21:00,314
[YOJI] You're leaving... Without
them?

322
00:21:01,647 --> 00:21:02,814
[VILLAGE CHIEF] We thank you.

323
00:21:02,914 --> 00:21:05,114
You'll always have... our utmost
gratitude.

324
00:21:10,547 --> 00:21:12,681
[SHINO] Take care of yourselves!

325
00:21:13,447 --> 00:21:14,947
[VILLAGERS] Thank you!

326
00:21:15,047 --> 00:21:18,014
You were a big help! Be well!

327
00:21:28,547 --> 00:21:31,547
[MARI] All right. So what are we
gonna do with the rest of them?

328
00:21:31,647 --> 00:21:32,681
[YOJI] Well...

329
00:21:39,514 --> 00:21:40,781
[YOJI] Refugees, right?

330
00:21:40,881 --> 00:21:44,114
[YOJI] Don't you worry... it'll
be fine!

331
00:21:50,814 --> 00:21:52,614
[MARI] (half‐laugh)

332
00:21:52,714 --> 00:21:55,214
[YOJI] Eh? Huh?
What're you smiling at?

333
00:21:55,314 --> 00:21:57,247
[MARI] Nothing.

334
00:21:57,347 --> 00:22:00,014
Just had a feeling you'd
say something like that.

335
00:22:02,581 --> 00:22:04,414
See? You do think I'm humane!

336
00:22:06,114 --> 00:22:08,547
[YOJI] Let's mount up, people!

337
00:22:08,647 --> 00:22:11,181
[YOJI] We're heading Alnus Hill!

338
00:23:45,714 --> 00:23:47,581
[LELEI] Next time on "GATE:"

339
00:23:47,681 --> 00:23:50,147
To the Land of the Unknown.

